OL,4,CCovid: Deaf woman wins claim over lack
OL,5,Cof sign language at briefings
OL,6, A deaf woman has won a claim against
OL,7, the government after a judge found a
OL,8, lack of sign language at two Covid
OL,9, briefings "served to disempower, to
OL,10, frustrate and to marginalise".
OL,12,FKatie Rowley, 36, from Leeds, started
OL,13,Fcourt action after the sessions went
OL,14,Fahead without interpreters on screen.
OL,16,FThe government denied breaching its
OL,17,Flegal obligation to make broadcasts
OL,18,Faccessible to deaf people.
OL,20,FIn his ruling, a judge said the lack of
OL,21,Fprovision constituted discrimination.
